DDeessccrriippttiioonn
       These functions manipulate the attributes  and  colour  of
       the window rendition of the current or specified window.

       The  and  functions obtain the current rendition of a win-
       dow.  If attrs or color_pair_number is a null pointer,  no
       information  will  be obtained on the corresponding rendi-
       tion information and this is not an error.

       The and functions turn off attrs in the current or  speci-
       fied window without affecting any others.

       The  and  functions turn on attrs in the current or speci-
       fied window without affecting any others.

       The and functions set the window rendition of the  current
       or specified window to attrs and color_pair_number.

       The  and functions set the window colour of the current or
       specified window to color_pair_number.

RReettuurrnn vvaalluuee
